				ent_hell

names {"entrance hell"}
title "The Entrance to the First Plane"
descr
"   After regaining your sense of direction, you realize your curiosity
may have cost you dearly this time. You stand looking out over the caverns
and fissures making up the first plane of hell. Most of this land is bare
but the heat is unbearable and occassionally small fires burst from the
ground all about you. You hear a very steady stream of moans and shrieks
from every direction. Directly in front of you a large gate of fire blocks
you from proceeding any further."
extra {"fiery gate", "gate"}
"   The material which forged this gate must be very fire retardant. A fire
whose intensity darkens your skin covers the entire gate. Upon closer
inspection you realize the flames engrossing the gate of hell are not hot.
You think you can actually touch it."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to plane1_rm1 open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED} descr
 "The gate to hell is there." keyword {"gate to hell", "gate", "fiery gate"};
/* Added by Papi, I didn't understand why it was missing... ? */
up to cave@volcano;
end

				plane1_rm1
title "The First Plane of hell"
descr
"   The fiery gates you passed through to get here are no longer visible
to your eyes. The feeling of being caged sets in and you become aware that
your survival depends on your powers of observation. You must battle the
psychic confusion cast about your very existence to get out of here, for it
is unlikely the exits, if any, will be easily found."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to plane1_rm2;
east to plane1_rm3;
west to plane1_rm4;
end

				plane1_rm2

title "the First Plane of hell"
descr
"   There seems to be no distinguishing features here at all. Every
direction yields a similar view, fiery caverns and brilliant red soil
covering the grounds beneath. Shadows dance and play formed from the
glow of several fires in the vicinty."
extra {"shadow", "shadows"}
"   They look like they could belong to any human-like form, but the
way they move is unlike that of anything you have known. Nothing in
the world you belong to can morph its body like this!"
extra {"fiery caverns", "caverns"}
"You cannot seem to to see very far inside, the scorching flames
block any visuals inside the caverns."
extra {"brilliant red soil", "red soil", "soil"}
"The soil seems unnaturally bright, as if the fires of hell burned inside
every grain!"
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
east to plane1_rm5;
west to plane1_rm6;
south to plane1_rm1;
end

