				rope_bridge
names {"rope bridge"}
title "A Rope Bridge"
descr
"   If you had a choice this bridge would surely not be traversed, but
you have a deep rooted feeling that you must cross it. Testing the bridge
reveals a rather unnerving creaking sound from the rope connections. There
is a lit cavern north of here and to the south is a door formed out of
a large boulder. Somehow you feel a bit relieved, your natural intuition
tells you this room lacks the magical barrier you sensed in every corner
of hell. Though you can not reach this realm through teleportation you
feel you can exit back to the mortal realm from here.
    There is a small hole in the floor of this area and if you enter
it you might possibly find your way out."
extra {"hole in the floor", "hole", "floor"}
"There is a small hole here in the floor. You can enter this
hole and teleport yourself back to safety."
extra {"boulder", "door"}
"There is a door formed from a boulder here."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_MOB, UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to lit_cavern1;
south to marble_court3 open {EX_OPEN_CLOSE, EX_CLOSED} descr
      "A small boulder door." keyword {"boulder", "door"};

/* Dil to allow safe passage back to the mortal realm. */

dilbegin prg2();
var
        pc      :       unitptr;
code
{
    :init:
    heartbeat := PULSE_SEC*5;

    :start:
    wait(SFB_CMD, ((command(CMD_ENTER)) and (("floor" in argument) or
        ("hole" in argument))));

    pc := activator;
    secure(pc, lost_pc);
    block;
    pause;
    act("You find yourself fading into another existance as you pass through.",
        A_ALWAYS, pc, null, null, TO_CHAR);
    act(pc.name+" enters the hole in the floor and vanishes.",
        A_SOMEONE, pc, null, null, TO_REST);
    link(pc, findroom("udgaard/temple"));
    act("You find yourself emerging in the temple of Udgaard.",
        A_ALWAYS, pc, null, null, TO_CHAR);
    goto start;

    :lost_pc:
    pause;
    goto start;
}
dilend

end

				lit_cavern1

names {"lit cavern"}
title "A Lit Cavern"
descr
"   Your nerves have a brief moment to rejoice after successfuly
traversing the shabby bridge. You now stand at the other end in
a somewhat lighted cavern. The only source you can see are the many
torches nailed into the cavern wall, and their fires look to be
dimming with every passing breath."
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
extra {"torches", "torch"}
"They are fastened to the cavern wall, unremovable but the do provide
a meager sort of light source for the time being."
movement SECT_INSIDE
north to large_cavern;
south to rope_bridge;
east to lit_cavern2;
west to lit_cavern3;
ALWAYS_LIGHT
end

				large_cavern
names {"large cavern", "cavern"}
title "A Large Cavern"
descr
"   You exit the lit cavern into a somewhat dismal one. You notice the
rock walls form a circular perimeter about the room and though you cannot
tell for sure, it seems almost perfectly symmetric. Besides the normal
rocks and dust scattered about the ground there is a large mat placed
in the center. The low lighting makes it difficult to see clearly though."
extra {"rock walls", "walls", "wall"}
"They are quite smooth, almost like they were specially created to be
such. The walls form a symmetric sphere about you."
extra {"rocks", "dust", "rock"}
"There are many rocks scattered about the ground, most likely the
remains of any jagged edges since removed. The dust is almost too
much for you, it is apparent the inhabitants do not suffer from
allergies."
extra {"large mat", "mat"}
"It is hard to discern the material this mat is made of, in fact
you can barely see it from here but it seems the room was formed
around it."
movement SECT_INSIDE
flags {UNIT_FL_NO_WEATHER}
south to lit_cavern1;
IN_ALWAYS_DARK
end

